Creamy Baked Mac and Cheese with Bacon

Presheat oven to 350 degrees
Place 2 1/2 cups of elbow macaroni in boiling water.
Boil for about 8 minutes.

Crush 1 sleeve of Ritz crackers and mix in 1/4 cup melted butter. Set aside.

In a large suace pot (On medium high) melt 1/4 cup butter and whisck in a 1/4 cup flour.
Whisk in 4 cups whole milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Whisck and bring to a boil stirring constantly until thick.  About 10 minutes.

Stir in  1/2 pound shredded chedder cheese and 1/2 pound shredded pepper jack cheese.  Add 1 pound cooked crumbled bacon.

Pour into a 9x13 inch pan.  Sprinkle crumb mixture over the top and bake for 45 minutes.  

Serves 12

Use White Whole Wheat Flour - King Author Flour
